{"title_page": "Petron Tri-Activ Spikers", "text_new": "{{short description|Philippines volleyball club}}\n{{Infobox volleyball club\n| clubname    = Petron Blaze Spikers\n| short name  = Petron Blaze\n| nickname    = Petron\n| image       = [[File:Petron Tri-Activ Spikers logo.png|200px]]\n| fullname    = \n| founded     = 2013\n| dissolved   = \n| ground      = \n| capacity    = \n| chairman    = \n| manager     = Ramon Cruz\n| captain     = [[Katherine Bell (volleyball)|Katherine Bell]]\n| league      = [[Philippine Super Liga|Philippine SuperLiga]]\n| season      = [[2019 PSL Grand Prix Conference|2019 Grand Prix]]\n| position    = '''Champions''' ({{increase}}1)\n| titles      = 5\n| website     = http://philippinesuperliga.com/wp/2017-filipino-conference-teams/petron/\n| pattern_b1  = _PetronTriActiv\n| pattern_ra1 = \n| pattern_s1  = \n| leftarm1    = FF0000\n| body1       = FFFFFF\n| rightarm1   = FF0000\n| shorts1     = #000BA8\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2  = _PetronTriActiv2\n| pattern_ra2 = \n| pattern_s2  = \n| leftarm2    = FF0000\n| body2       = #000BA8 \n| rightarm2   = FF0000\n| shorts2     = #000BA8\n| current     = \n}}\n\nThe '''Petron Blaze Spikers'''<ref name=\"Petron Blaze Spikers\">{{cite web|url=http://philippinesuperliga.com/wp/teams/psl-grand-prix-womens-teams/petron-blaze-spikers/|title=Petron Blaze Spikers|publisher=}}</ref> are a professional women's volleyball team playing in the [[Philippine Super Liga|Philippine SuperLiga]] (PSL). The team is owned by [[Petron Corporation]]. The company's involvement in volleyball began in 2002, when it established the Petron Ladies Beach Volleyball Tournament.\n\n==Team history==\nPetron became the first team to sweep a PSL tournament with a 13\u20130 record and claim the [[2015 PSL All-Filipino Conference|2015 All-Filipino]] championship, its second consecutive PSL title.<ref>[http://sports.inquirer.net/181562/petron-blazes-new-superliga-title-trail Petron blazes new Superliga title trail], sports.inquirer.net, February 19, 2017</ref><ref>[http://www.philstar.com/sports/2015/05/15/1454951/superligas-super-sweep-petron-blaze-beats-shopinas-psl-crown Superliga\u2019s super sweep Petron Blaze beats Shopinas for PSL crown], philstar.com, February 19, 2017</ref><ref>[http://sports.tempo.com.ph/2015/05/15/petron-wins-2nd-superliga-crown/ Petron wins 2nd superliga crown] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150530042234/http://sports.tempo.com.ph/2015/05/15/petron-wins-2nd-superliga-crown/ |date=2015-05-30 }}, sports.tempo.com.ph, February 19, 2017</ref> At their stint in the [[2015 Asian Women's Club Volleyball Championship]] in Ha Nam, Vietnam, the team finished at 8th place with only one game won out of six matches played.\n\nOn September 12, 2016, the team parted ways with coach George Pascua. He was replaced by Cesael \"Shaq\" delos Santos.<ref>[http://tiebreakertimes.com/tbt/source-pascua-out-as-petron-coach/66169 SOURCE: Pascua out as Petron coach], tiebreakertimes.com, September 12, 2016</ref>\n\n==Name changes==\n===Indoor volleyball===\n*'''Petron Blaze Spikers''' ([[2013 PSL season|2013]]-[[2015 PSL season|2015]], [[2017 PSL season|2017]]-present)\n*'''Petron Tri-Activ Spikers''' ([[2016 PSL season|2016]])\n\n===Beach volleyball===\n*'''Petron Sprint 4T''' (Petron Team A - [[2015 PSL Beach Volleyball Challenge Cup|2015]]-[[2017 PSL Beach Volleyball Challenge Cup|2017]])\n*'''Petron XCS''' (Petron Team B - [[2015 PSL Beach Volleyball Challenge Cup|2015]]-[[2017 PSL Beach Volleyball Challenge Cup|2017]]; solo team - [[2018 PSL Beach Volleyball Challenge Cup|2018]])\n\n==Current roster==\nFor the [[2020 PSL Grand Prix Conference]]:\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:130%; text-align:center; width:30%;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style= \"background: red; color: blue; text-align: center\" | '''Petron Blaze Spikers'''\n|- \n!style=\"width:3em; background:navy; color:white;\"|No.\n!style=\"width:16em; background:navy; color:white;\"|Name\